import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    job_counts = data['job'].value_counts()
    job_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6), color='c')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job types in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Job Types')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(['Job Types'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    yearly_job_count = data.groupby('year')['count'].sum().reset_index()

    plt.plot(yearly_job_count['year'], yearly_job_count['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Job Count')
    plt.title('How does the count of jobs vary by year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='sex', values='count', aggfunc='sum')
    pivot_data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))

    plt.title("What is the distribution of job count by sex?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Job Count")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Sex")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(index='job', columns='year', values='count', aggfunc='sum')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 12))
    sns.heatmap(pivot_data, cmap='coolwarm', linewidths=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count by job type and year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Job Type')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(rotation=0)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_agg = data.groupby('job')['perc'].sum().reset_index()
    data_agg = data_agg.sort_values(by='perc', ascending=False)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.pie(data_agg['perc'], labels=data_agg['job'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of percentage of jobs by job type?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
